HEADWORD: Imbrangle
<hw>Im*bran"gle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To entangle as
in a cobweb; to mix confusedly.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Hudibras.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Physiology <qex>imbrangled</qex> with an inapplicable logic.</q>
<rj><qau>Coleridge.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Imbreed</ent>⟦br⟧
